OL,5, Four out of every 10 pupils have       
OL,6, difficulty accessing free period       
OL,7, products in UK schools, research shared
OL,8, with BBC News suggests.                
OL,10,FGovernment schemes to reduce stigma and
OL,11,Fimprove access have been running for   
OL,12,Fseveral years - and many schools say   
OL,13,Fthese have benefited pupils.           
OL,15,FIt says 97% of secondary schools in    
OL,16,FEngland have ordered the free products.
OL,18,FBut some teenagers are still feeling   
OL,19,Fupset, angry and embarrassed about     
OL,20,Fdealing with their period at school.   
